  <mainDescription>&lt;P>Project key stakeholder roles can be classified into the six following categories:&lt;/P>
&lt;P style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=ltr>&lt;STRONG>1. Business Governing Layer&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/P>
&lt;P style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=ltr>This layer determines the vision and strategy for the organization as a whole. It consists of one or more management committees operating at a high or the highest management&amp;nbsp;level.&amp;nbsp; Appropriate Governance Body (AGB) is the corresponding role.&lt;/P>
&lt;P>&lt;STRONG>2. Steering Layer&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/P>
&lt;P>This layer provides general project direction and guidance. It keeps the project focused on its objectives and reports to the AGB. The Project Steering Committee is composed of four roles, namely, Project Owner (PO), Solution Provider (SP), Business Manager (BM) and Project Manager (PM).&lt;/P>
&lt;P>&lt;STRONG>3. Directing Layer&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/P>
&lt;P>This layer champions the project and owns its Business Case. It mobilizes the necessary resources and monitors the project's performance in order to realize the project's objectives. It comprises the roles of Project Owner (PO) and Solution Provider (SP)&lt;/P>
&lt;P>&lt;STRONG>4. Managing Layer&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/P>
&lt;P style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>The Managing Layer focuses on day-to-day project management. It organises, monitors and controls work to produce the intended deliverables and implement them in the business organisation. Members of the Managing Layer report to the Directing Layer. The Managing Layer comprises the roles of Business Manager (BM) and Project Manager (PM). It is of utmost importance for the success of the project that there is close collaboration and good communication between these two roles.&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>
&lt;P style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>&lt;/SPAN>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P>
&lt;P style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>&lt;STRONG>5. Performing Layer&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>
&lt;P style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>&lt;STRONG>&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/SPAN>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>
&lt;P class=PM2-Body style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>The Performing Layer carries out the project work. It produces the deliverables and implements them in the business organisation. Members of the Performing Layer report to the Managing Layer. The Performing Layer comprises the roles of the Business Implementation Group (BIG) and the Project Core Team (PCT).&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>
&lt;P class=PM2-Body style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>&lt;/SPAN>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P>
&lt;P class=PM2-Body style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>&lt;STRONG>6. Project Support Team&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>
&lt;P class=PM2-Body style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>&lt;STRONG>&lt;/STRONG>&lt;/SPAN>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P>
&lt;P class=PM2-Body style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>This category comprises the following optional roles: Project Support Office (PSO), Project Quality Assurance (PQA), Project Manager Assistant (PMA) and Contractor's Project Manager (CPM). &lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>
&lt;P class=PM2-Body style=&quot;MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;>&lt;SPAN lang=EN-GB style=&quot;mso-ansi-language: EN-GB&quot;>&lt;/SPAN>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P>
